Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Line a #baking sheet{} with foil and brush with oil (or coat with nonstick spray). Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced); mince a few slices until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion; cook for ~{3%minutes}.

Add @ground beef{10%oz} and @southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}; cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until beef is browned and onion is softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @tex-mex paste{1} and 1/3 cup water (½ cup for 4 servings). Simmer until mixture has thickened and beef is cooked through, ~{2-4%minutes} more. Turn off heat.

Meanwhile, drizzle @flour tortillas{6} with 1 TBSP @olive oil{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings); brush or rub to completely coat both sides.

Place tortillas on a clean work surface. Once beef filling is done, add a heaping ¼ cup filling to one side of each tortilla, then sprinkle each with 1 TBSP @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup}.

Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to create flautas. Place, seam sides down, on prepared #sheet{}. TIP: Make sure the flautas are snug on the sheet—this will prevent them from unrolling.

Bake on middle rack until golden brown and crispy, ~{8-12%minutes}.

While flautas bake, finely dice @tomato{1}(finely diced). In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato and minced onion. Season with @salt{}.

Divide flautas between plates. Top with pico de gallo and @smoky red pepper crema{4%tbsp}. Serve.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.